<div class='faqsQuestionContainer'>
	<div id='stairwayMeasuringHelp' class='faqsQuestion'>
		I'm trying to place an order for railings for my stairway, but you guys are asking me to estimate the length of railing needed.
		How do I do that?!
	</div>
	<div class='faqsQuestionUnderline'></div>
	<p class='faqsAnswer'>
		Pretty simple. First, count the number of steps on your stairway. Then figure out the length of railing needed for
		the landing area (the area where the steps leads into). After that, add both numbers together to figure out the
		number of feet of railing needed for your stairway. For example, check out the picture below.
		<br />
		<img src='client/images/landing-area.jpg' />
		<br />
		In the picture above, let's say railings are needed along the left edge of the porch (where the arrows are).
		The red arrow represents the railing needed for the stairs while the purple arrow represents the railing needed
		for the landing area. Since we have three steps, we need three feet of railing for the stairs alone. The landing area
		at the top of the stairs spans two feet (from the top step to the door). Altogether, we need five feet
		of railing for the left edge of the stairs.
		<br />
		Rarely do measurements round out nicely to whole numbers, however. Likely, whatever final number you end up with
		will be a decimal value. In that case, just round the number to the nearest whole number. So let's say you
		need 7.4 feet of railing, just round that figure down to 7 feet. And don't worry about giving us a number that's
		not exact - when we come by to confirm your measurements, we will take note of the exact length.
		<br />
		Please keep in mind that if the stairwell features curves that need to be railed, then please give up
		trying to measure out the length yourself and <a href='/contactUs' class='spaceBeforeAndAfter'>reach out to us</a>
		so that we can handle it.
	</p>
</div>

<div class='faqsQuestionContainer'>
	<div id='deckMeasuringHelp' class='faqsQuestion'>
		I'm trying to place an order for railings for my deck/balcony/enclosure, but you guys are asking me to estimate
		the length of railing needed. How do I do that?!
	</div>
	<div class='faqsQuestionUnderline'></div>
	<p class='faqsAnswer'>
		Even simpler than measuring the length of railing needed for stairways. Just measure the edges of your deck that will need
		to be railed in. Sum up all those measurements and you'll figure out the length of railing in feet that's needed.
		Any part of the deck that is lined up against a wall or an opening should not be measured. That's it.
		Honestly, think back to the days of your childhood when you were sitting in math class learning about how to
		calculate the perimeters of geometrical figures. It took awhile, but you could finally apply those skills here!
		<br />
		Rarely do measurements round out nicely to whole numbers, however. Likely, whatever final number you end up with
		will be a decimal value. In that case, just round that number to the nearest whole number. So let's say you
		need 9.6 feet of railing, just round that figure up to 10 feet. And don't worry about giving us a number that's
		not exact - when we come by to confirm your measurements, we will take note of the exact length.
		<br />
		Please keep in mind that if your deck has any curves need to be railed, then at that point, give up trying to
		measure out the length yourself and <a href='/contactUs' class='spaceBeforeAndAfter'>reach out to us</a> so that
		we can handle it.
	</p>
</div>

