<div class='faqsQuestionContainer'>
	<div class='faqsQuestion'>
		How do you install your railings?
	</div>
	<div class='faqsQuestionUnderline'></div>
	<p class='faqsAnswer'>
		Using a small <a href='https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Core_drill' class='spaceBefore'>core drill</a>, we drill holes into the ground several
		inches deep so that we can place the posts that will support the railings. Any gaps in the holes are then filled
		with a specialized cement that will not expand or contract regardless of the weather. The cement only takes up to
		one hour to fully dry and lock the posts into place.
		<br /><br />
		Of course, we will NOT be using a core drill if the railings need to be anchored into wood or somewhere inside a
		building. Instead, we use metal plates. Metal plates will be welded onto the bottom of the posts. Those same
		metal plates will then be screwed directly into the wood or floor in order to ensure the stability of our railings.
	</p>
</div>

